HEADWORD: Brokenness
<hw>Bro"ken*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or
quality of being broken; unevenness.</def>
<rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contrition; <as>as, <ex>brokenness</ex> of
heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Broken wind</ent>⟦br⟧
